cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about language models, specifically syntactic language models and their performance compared to sequential language models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge distillation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions targeted syntactic evaluations, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as syntactic analysis is often used in natural language processing tasks such as image captioning.
